  "schema_version": "1.7.4",
  "id": "",
  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated code across many bundled modules under.ad/ directory",
  "details": "The package ships 45+ JavaScript files under a hidden-style `.ad/` directory (x0.js through xz.js, plus from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js) that are heavily obfuscated using hex-encoded identifier names (e.g., `_0x5d12be`, `_0x1f3ce7`). The file naming scheme (single-letter alphabet enumeration) and the breadth of obfuscated content are unusual for a legitimate library. Filenames such as `phone-validator.js`, `sms-providers.js`, and `smtp-health-cache.js` suggest functionality around messaging/email infrastructure that is not consistent with most general-purpose libraries and warrants manual inspection. Tracing of execution paths did not complete, so the actual behavior of these modules (lifecycle hooks, network destinations, credential access) was not verified. Without that corroboration, an automatic block on obfuscation alone would risk false positives, but the volume and pattern of obfuscation is sufficiently anomalous to require human review before allowing installs.",
